# Vite+ tooling

Use root scripts backed by Vite+ (`vp` global CLI + local `vite-plus`). Do not use `npx vp`. Do not bypass with a globally installed oxlint/oxfmt/vitest outside Vite+.

| Task | Command |
|---|---|
| Install locked dependencies | `vp install` (or `npm ci`) |
| Start web development | `npm run dev` → `vp dev apps/web` |
| Format | `npm run format` → `vp fmt` |
| Lint | `npm run lint` → `vp lint` |
| Format, lint, and type-check | `npm run check` → `vp check` |
| Run Vitest once | `npm test` → `vp test` |
| Run coverage | `npm run test:coverage` |
| Build `apps/web` | `npm run build` → `vp build apps/web` |
| Preview build | `npm run preview` → `vp preview apps/web` |
| Workspace typecheck | `npm run typecheck` → `vp run -r typecheck` |
| CLI playground | `npm run cli -- <cmd>` |
| Diagnose Vite+ syntax | `vp help` or `vp <command> --help` |

## Layout

- Root `vite.config.ts`: fmt, lint, staged, shared test includes, monorepo `overrides`.
- `apps/web/vite.config.ts`: app resolve aliases + Vitest project; later TanStack Start + Cloudflare plugin.
- `apps/cli`: **no** `vite-plus` dependency — covered by root fmt/lint only; runtime is `tsx`.

## Change discipline

- Pin `vite-plus` and keep root `overrides.vite` → `@voidzero-dev/vite-plus-core` in lockstep.
- Commit `package-lock.json`.
- Prefer `vp add` / `vp install` for dependency changes.
- Import tests from `vite-plus/test`, never directly from `vitest`.
- Discover unfamiliar flags with local `vp … --help`; do not guess.
- Do not add a second formatter, linter, test runner, or independent app build pipeline without an ADR.
- Do not reintroduce a Vercel-only build pipeline as the Must path.
